It includes open-ended questions for session details and comments, and rubric-based scoring for nine key competencies (Identification, Situation, Background, etc.), each scored from 0 to 3. The Global Rating Scale (GRS) is also scored from 0 to 3. Each respondent provides a complete set of scores and comments for a specific session. The data is organized by respondent, with each respondent's session and performance metrics clearly listed.
